{
  "texts": [
    "Jellyfish bridges the gap between adaptive video analytics systems and inference serving systems.",
    "Joint adaptation Recent works have also argued for joint data and DNN adaptation.",
    "However, they either focus on a single-client setup (Nigade et al. 2021) or optimize resources with relatively lenient latency constraints (i.e., 1-5s) (Jiang et al. 2021).",
    "In contrast, Jellyfish maximizes inference accuracy with millisecondlevel latency SLO targets given a highly dynamic network.",
    "Dynamic DNNs Recently, neural architecture search (NAS) based methods such as ProxylessNAS (Cai et al. 2019), MnasNet (Tan et al. 2019), and OFA (Cai et al. 2020) have been proposed to generate dynamic (or static) sub-networks by searching through the large architecture space."
  ]
}